<br>
So far I haven't seen anything I'd want to spend my points on. I could add procs to my weapons... but do I really want more agro from something like a lifetap proc? I can add stats... my str is maxed, I suppose a little extra agi gets me a little extra AC. And my sta isn't quite maxed. And I can get +hp augments. But that really isn't changing much for a rogue. <br>
<br>
I suppose I can get vengance augments (if they are type 1). I suppose eventually I might see some okay loot, allegedly you can eventually get a 17 damage piercer through LDoN. But where's the fun stuff? The augment system is too restrictive and the points amased too slowly to let you play around.<br>
<br>
Maybe things will pick up. Maybe once I have lots of points I'll find stuff I want. LDoN is fun but I think risk reward needs to be tweaked. Like someone said above, normal should be made into easy, and there should be a medium mid way between easy and hard. And the raids, you shouldn't have to be elemental equipped to do a LDoN raid.<br>
<br>
I think a lot of the problem is that once you are in the 60s, you're all lumped together. You have the 61st level person with no AAs and mediocre gear and you have 65th level person with 250 AAs and elemental gear. Easy is too easy, hard is too hard.<br>
<br>
Don't get me wrong, LDoN is a lot of fun. But I'm holding my breath for improvements and tweaks to make it more worthwhile.<br>
