<br>
Well, yeah there are some great things you could get with 5000 points.<br>
<br>
But that's what 100 mission?<br>
<br>
For every single item?<br>
<br>
When I thought of augments, I was hoping to see a more continuous progression. That is to say, you might get an augment every few adventures, which over time stack up to something pretty considerable. With so many augment restrictions that's just not how the augment system works. Augment does not mean a change to lots of smaller upgrades rather than one big upgrade once in a blue moon. I guess that's what I'm getting at. I was hoping that I could make a little progress every few adventures by adding an augment to my gear, rather than saving up for ages to buy 1 piece of gear and 3 augments as it seems to be. Sure, I do make a little progress each adventure... but only in the form of &quot;points&quot;.<br>
<br>
I prefer little and often to big and rare. In the end they would be the same power, but you'd see the steps forward rather than just burying yourself in a timesink<br>
<br>
Shackleton <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=borblefootfurtoe>borblefoot furtoe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 232<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/17/03 2:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4049.topic&index=34>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_supermad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: 8 min.....</span><hr size=1> Hmm I have added about 10 wisdom and 5 MR and 5 PR and 10 DR via augments that dropped in dungeons so far. Sometimes none drop but I have found that on average 1 or 2 will drop per dungeon.<br>
