<br>
I had a pretty long post written up about what makes gear nice to wear for melee, but let's just keep this simple.  If you think there's something nice out there, post a link or post the item with stats.  I've seen the safehouse list and a couple of others (as well as the LDON item db site).  Pretty pathetic when it comes to melee items.  If you think you're goin to get nice gear from LDON, you're mistaken.<br>
<br>
What you will get from LDON items is a huge time sink for a single item,  another time sink to augment the resists, and another to augment the effects.   Your final item will be easily upgraded by a single raid-drop in all particulars.  All your LDON efforts, three sets of 20-30 missions, replaced by a single raid drop.<br>
<br>
Don't spend your AP points on items or augments that are anything less than final.  It's just not worth it.  LDON is not for items.  It's for fun dungeon crawls. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=delandril>Delandril</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 188<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/17/03 7:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4049.topic&index=36>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: So, uh, where are these amazing items?</span><hr size=1> There are very few dungeons where the 1000+ point gear can be found...of that stuff, most of it is VERY nice. Given time, I think you guys will see that if you have enough points to spend, you can get some very high quality gear....I'll see if I can dig up the post I found earlier...<br>
